description: Detach the control modules from module 1 to module 6 from the circuit, then attach them between the PSU and load modules and check if the lamp turns on. , outcome='ANOMALOUS\n\nThe subchain test from cube_ctrl1 to cube_ctrl6 resulted in the lamp remaining OFF, indicating that there is an issue with at least one control module in this segment. No observable internal fault was detected in the bulb itself, so the anomaly likely resides within one or more of the modules (DetachedSwitch1 through DetachedSwitch6). Further isolation is needed to identify the specific faulty module(s).\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=330.0, cost_breakdown=[('detach_sequence_of_control_modules_and_attach_it_to_power_and_load', 320.0), ('observe_component', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> ControlSubsystem,
description: Detach the control modules from module 1 to module 3 from the circuit, then attach them between the PSU and load modules and check if the lamp turns on. , outcome='NOMINAL. The lamp turns ON when control modules 1 to 3 are directly connected between PSU and load, indicating that the subchain [DetachedSwitch1, DetachedSwitch2, DetachedSwitch3] is functioning correctly. No faults are present in this sequence.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=320.0, cost_breakdown=[('detach_sequence_of_control_modules_and_attach_it_to_power_and_load', 320.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
