description: Detach the control modules from module 1 to module 4 from the circuit, then attach them between the PSU and load modules and check if the lamp turns on. , outcome='NOMINAL\n\nThe subchain test for control modules cube_ctrl1 through cube_ctrl4 is NOMINAL: when these modules are connected between the PSU and the load, the lamp turns ON. This means all these modules in the tested subchain are functioning correctly.\n\nNote: The later visual inspection found the main bulb not lit at that moment, but this does not contradict the subchain test result, since the subchain test explicitly reported the lamp turning ON during the test.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=330.0, cost_breakdown=[('detach_sequence_of_control_modules_and_attach_it_to_power_and_load', 320.0), ('observe_component', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
